# Flask API Commands

## Activate Virtual Environment

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
```

Activates the local Python virtual environment so commands use this project's installed packages.

## Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Installs all Python packages listed in `requirements.txt`.

## Run the App

```bash
flask --app wsgi run
```

Starts the Flask development server using `wsgi.py` as the app entry point.

## Initialize Migrations

```bash
flask --app wsgi db init
```

Creates the `migrations/` folder for Alembic/Flask-Migrate.

Run this only once when setting up migrations for the first time.

## Generate a Migration

```bash
flask --app wsgi db migrate -m "create users table"
```

Creates a new migration file based on changes in SQLAlchemy models.

This command only creates the migration file. It does not update the database.

## Apply Migrations

```bash
flask --app wsgi db upgrade
```

Applies pending migration files to the database.

Use this after generating or pulling new migrations.

## Roll Back Last Migration

```bash
flask --app wsgi db downgrade
```

Reverts the most recent database migration.

Use this carefully because it can remove tables, columns, or data depending on the migration.

## Common Development Flow

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
flask --app wsgi db migrate -m "describe your model change"
flask --app wsgi db upgrade
flask --app wsgi run
```

This flow activates the environment, creates a migration, applies it to the database, and starts the app.
